default&#xa0;
defaultsee themselves as having no political power in Sark at all and therefore find it extremely surprising that it should be suggested that they threaten democracy on that Island.
default&#xa0;
defaultMy clients believe that the true history of Sark politics and what passes for democracy over the last few years has been the domination of Sark by a clique which has the 
defaultSeigneur
default and the Seneschal at its centre.
default&#xa0;
default The reforms which took place in Sark have affected matters hardly at all.
default&#xa0;
default Indeed the 
defaultSeigneur
default continues to sit on a dais in Chief Pleas with his appointee for life, the Seneschal, at his side, controlling and conducting the business of Chief Pleas.
default&#xa0;
